sql:
SELECT campaign_name
FROM marketing_analysis
WHERE roi > 2;

external_knowledge:
- The customer lifetime value (CLV) is a key metric that represents the total value a customer is expected to bring to a business over their lifetime; 
- The customer acquisition cost (CAC) is the cost of convincing a customer to buy a product or service; 
- The return on investment (ROI) is a financial metric that shows the gain (or loss) of an investment, relative to its cost; 
- A profit margin is a measure of a company's profitability, calculated by dividing net income by revenue; 
- The campaign success rate is the percentage of campaigns that achieve their desired outcome.
